sentences: They had success with an international single "Radiation" that used vocal samples from 1952 movie "Duck and Cover".
In 2004 he was the first American breakbeat DJ to complete a DJ club tour throughout India.
In 2006, David was signed to Six Degrees Records and released 2 albums and 5 EP's.
He performed with a full band dubbed the "David Starfire Live Ensemble Ensemble" from 2009 to 2013 and featured various musicians, vocalists, and dancers.
In 2014, David created his own label, Amrita Recordings, with worldwide distribution through Label Engine.
In 2016, David released his Karuna album where he traveled to the Thai-Burma border-zones to collaborate with Burmese refugee musicians, which was a first for an electronic artist.
In 2010 David Starfire co-founded the band "The Dub Kirtan All Stars" with Freq Nasty.

sentences: The band released "Bhakti Juggernaut" in 2015, there were previous song versions released on an EP and single.

sentences: Chaytanya, one of the main singers, was nominated for a Grammy in 2016 for her work on the "Bhakti Without Borders" album by Madi Das.

sentences: Bollyhood Bass Remixes Vol. 2 (Six Degrees Records 2011)
He has performed at international festivals including Burning Man, Coachella, Winter Music Conference, Love Parade, Lightning in a Bottle, and Outside Lands.
At 8 years old, David first had piano lessons and then moved to the guitar, which was his preferred instrument.
In the summer of his 18th birthday, he recorded the entire Moving Pictures album by RUSH and playing all the instruments himself.
It was suggested that David form a band and created Stain, which lasted about a year.
He then co-wrote songs with Jonathan Lacey from the band The Beautiful (the drummer, Frank, is now with Guns N' Roses) for about a year with Paul Slocum.
His unique style of mixing Indian and Middle Eastern sounds with electronic western music led to several DJ gigs in the West Coast and then beyond.
The band is currently on hiatus due to the busy schedules of the members.
